                        <interp inst="t18610610-name-88" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS TOWNSEND</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Police-sergeant, H</hi> 6). I produce a certificate—<hi rend="italic">Read: "Central Criminal Court, May, 1852; John Martin convicted of stealing a</hi>
               </p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186106100015"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">purse and money of a certain woman unknown, he having been before con<lb></lb>victed; 
Transported for Ten Years"</hi>)—The prisoner Martin is the person there referred to—I was present—he was not in my custody—I was in the case.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">MARTIN</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">
GUILTY</hi>.—<hi rend="italic">
